erequireddescriptionschema","need","none","number","numberofelements","object","of","offset","ok","openapi","or","order","other","page","pageable","pageableobject","paged","pagenumber","pagesize","pagestaffresponse","parameterintyperequireddescription","parameters","part","path","personname","practitioner","premises","present","probation","progress","provide","query","record","records","reference","referral","referrals","related","relevant","requested","required","respond","responds","responses","schemas","screen","service","size","sort","sorted","sortobject","staff","staffcode","staffgrade","staffresponse","statusdescriptionschema","string","support","supporting","surname","swagger","team","teamcoderesponse","teamcodes","teams","technical","that","the","these","to","totalelements","totalpages","true","ui","unpaged","unsorted","up","user","users","v1.0","via","view","we","when","who","with","workers","workload","yaml"],"pipeline":["trimmer"]}, "docs": {"11":{"title":"About","content":"Approved Premises and Delius\nService that responds to Approved Premises domain events, calls the\nHMPPS Approved Premises API\nand records referral progress against the probation case record in Delius. We\nalso provide an API to give probation case information to support making\napproved premises referrals.\nBusiness Need\nSupporting the Approved Premises service with the correct information required\nto make an Approved Premises application and ensuring the Probation\nPractitioner has an up-to-date view of activity in the Approved Premises\nservice when interacting with the probation case via Delius.\nContext Maps\n\n","url":"/"},"13":{"title":"API Reference","content":"\n    \n    API Reference\n\n\n.technical-documentation \u003e h1 { display: none !important }\nThe following documentation is also available in these formats:\n\n\nOpenAPI JSON\nOpenAPI YAML\nSwagger UI\n\nAPI Reference v1.0\n\n\n\n\n\n\n/teams/managingCase/{crn}\n\nget\n\n  List all teams involved in managing the probation case\n\n\n  A probation case may be managed by staff members who\n            are associated with multiple teams in Delius. Approve Premises users\n            need to view all applications that may be covered by direct colleagues\n            in order to cover absence and other workload-related issues. Respond\n            with a list of every team code that covers the probation case identified\n            by the CRN to enable the Approved Premises service to present the\n            relevant list of Approved Premises applications to it’s users.\n\n\n\n\nParameters\n\n\nParameterInTypeRequiredDescription\n\n\n\n\ncrn\npath\nstring\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n\nstaffCode\nquery\nstring\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponses\n\n\nStatusDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\n200\n\nOK\n\n\n\n{\n  \"teamCodes\": [\n    {\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n\n\nTeamCodeResponse\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n/approved-premises/{code}/staff\n\nget\n\n  List all members of staff that are keyworkers in the Approved Premises\n\n\n  An Approved Premises is defined in Delius as part of reference data.\n            Probation staff members can be linked to an Approved Premises as either staff\n            members or keyworkers via the “Approved Premises and Teams” screen of the Delius\n            user interface. Keyworkers are defined via the “Approved Premises and Key Workers”\n            screen of the Delius user interface. Respond with a list of all members of staff\n            defined as keyworkers for the Approved Premises identified by the requested code.\n\n\n\n\nParameters\n\n\nParameterInTypeRequiredDescription\n\n\n\n\ncode\npath\nstring\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n\nkeyWorker\nquery\nboolean\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n\npageable\nquery\nobject\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponses\n\n\nStatusDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\n200\n\nOK\n\n\n\n{\n  \"totalPages\": \"integer\",\n  \"totalElements\": \"integer\",\n  \"size\": \"integer\",\n  \"content\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"string\",\n      \"name\": {\n        \"forename\": \"string\",\n        \"surname\": \"string\",\n        \"middleName\": \"string\"\n      },\n      \"grade\": {\n        \"code\": \"string\",\n        \"description\": \"string\"\n      },\n      \"keyWorker\": \"boolean\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"number\": \"integer\",\n  \"sort\": {\n    \"empty\": \"boolean\",\n    \"sorted\": \"boolean\",\n    \"unsorted\": \"boolean\"\n  },\n  \"first\": \"boolean\",\n  \"last\": \"boolean\",\n  \"numberOfElements\": \"integer\",\n  \"pageable\": {\n    \"offset\": \"integer\",\n    \"sort\": {\n      \"empty\": \"boolean\",\n      \"sorted\": \"boolean\",\n      \"unsorted\": \"boolean\"\n    },\n    \"paged\": \"boolean\",\n    \"pageNumber\": \"integer\",\n    \"pageSize\": \"integer\",\n    \"unpaged\": \"boolean\"\n  },\n  \"empty\": \"boolean\"\n}\n\n\n\nPageStaffResponse\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSchemas\nTeamCodeResponse\n\n\n\n\nNameTypeRequiredDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\nteamCodes\narray\ntrue\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPageable\n\n\n\n\nNameTypeRequiredDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\npage\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nsize\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nsort\narray\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPageStaffResponse\n\n\n\n\nNameTypeRequiredDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\ntotalPages\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\ntotalElements\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nsize\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\ncontent\narray\nfalse\n\n\n  StaffResponse\n\n\n\n\nnumber\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nsort\nobject\nfalse\n\n\n  SortObject\n\n\n\n\nfirst\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nlast\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nnumberOfElements\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\npageable\nobject\nfalse\n\n\n  PageableObject\n\n\n\n\nempty\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPageableObject\n\n\n\n\nNameTypeRequiredDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\noffset\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nsort\nobject\nfalse\n\n\n  SortObject\n\n\n\n\npaged\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\npageNumber\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\npageSize\ninteger\nfalse\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\nunpaged\nboolean\nf